<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEMS DIAGNOSTICS - Circuit Diagnostics -
        Controller Area Network (CAN) Communications
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Controller Area Network (CAN) Communications</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="d3363" filename="../figd33/D3363.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Function Diagram for the Controller Area Network (CAN)</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The Function Diagram for the CAN includes the following:</para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Drivetrain Datalink (CAN 1)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Terminating resistors - 120 ohm</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>ENGINE lamp (amber)</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>
            </para>
            <para>The Drivetrain Datalink is a Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) term referring to one of the
                datalinks common to all trucks. The Drivetrain Datalink is the communication link for the Electronic
                Control Module (ECM), Electronic System Controller (ESC), and the instrument panel. The Drivetrain
                Datalink is also used for power train communication and control.
            </para>
            <para>The engine controller transmits component information across the Drivetrain Datalink to the instrument
                panel. The following instrument panel components are in constant communication with the Drivetrain
                Datalink:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Oil pressure gauge</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine oil temperature gauge</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Tachometer</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Speedometer</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Odometer / hourmeter</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Coolant temperature gauge</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Coolant level lamp</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine red lamp</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Engine amber lamp</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Change oil message</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cruise / PTO control</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Wait to Start lamp</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>The ECM and ESC use the Drivetrain Datalink to provide the instrument panel with status information on
                the following features.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Cruise control ON/OFF</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cruise control Set / Cruise</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cruise control resume / accelerate</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Cruise control clutch</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Brake pedal</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>AC demand</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Self-test input</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Remote Accelerator Pedal (RPS)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>In-Cab PTO / Throttle switch</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection / Management</title>
            </para>
            <para>There are no engine DTCs for CAN 1 communications.</para>
            <para>
                <title>Tools</title>
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Electronic Service Tool (EST) with Master Diagnostics software</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>International&#174; EZ-Tech Interface Cable</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Digital Multimeter (DMM)</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>See truck Chassis Electrical Circuit Diagram and Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>CAN Pin Point Diagnostics</title>
            <figure id="f24007" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic id="d3364" filename="../figd33/D3364.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="432px"/>
                <caption>CAN Communication Circuit Diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="te24007022" tblwidth="pg-wide" frame="bottom">
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="2.00in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <warning>
                                    <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or
                                        vehicle, always disconnect main negative battery cable first. Always connect the
                                        main negative battery cable last.
                                    </para>
                                </warning>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Voltage Checks</emph>
                                    (Check at EST connector with Key ON Engine OFF.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0">
                                <para>Signal</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>B to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>B+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0">
                                <para>Power</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Should be B+ power at B all times. If no power, check ground and power circuits.
                                    See truck Chassis Electrical Circuit Diagram manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>C to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>C+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0">
                                <para>Power</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Should be between 2-7V.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">Resistance Checks</emph>
                                    (Turn ignition key OFF. Check at EST connector with negative battery cable
                                    disconnected.)
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>C to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>1M&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>CAN+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If &#60;1M&#x2126;, a short between CAN+ and ground exists. Disconnect ECM X3 and
                                    check again. If short is no longer present, replace ECM. If short exists, harness or
                                    other node component defective.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>D to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>1M&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>CAN-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If &#60;1M&#x2126;, a short between CAN - and ground exists. Disconnect ECM X3 and
                                    check again. If short is no longer present, replace ECM. If short still exists,
                                    harness or other node component defective.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>C to D</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>60&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0">
                                <para>CAN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>The datalink has two terminating resistors in parallel of 120&#x2126; each. If >70&#x2126;,
                                    check for missing terminating resister or open in the CAN+ or CAN - wires. If &#60;50&#x2126;,
                                    check for extra terminating resistor. If &#60;5&#x2126;, check for short between
                                    CAN+ and CAN -.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
